content.description: A hand and fist crack in a right facing corner, just left of the three bolt face called Fast Foods.
content.protection: Bring the rack for a 50 foot hand and fist crack.

content.description: A three bolt 5.8 leads up to an anchor at 50 feet.  A rare, "easy", sport pitch.  It is a slab, not a hueco pull.
content.protection: Quickdraws and maybe some gear to set up directional anchors for the neighboring cracks.
content.location: This route is easy to find because it's the only bolted face around.  There is also a nice 5.7 crack on the left margin of the bolted slab called Short Hands.

content.description: Begin sitting with crimp-edge hueco. Move up to the sloper, and make a hard move out left. Continue up to top on good huecos.
content.location: Brainwashed boulder, a bit north of end loop parking area and old concrete slabs. Faces east, away from the road.

content.description: This is the line immediately left of Brainwashed V4 on the same boulder. According to two pretty credible sources it has never been done. Its also not in the new guidebook. The problem is really hard; it took me a good hour of trying everything other than a jump to realize that it was the only way. The issue with the jump is that there are two huge rocks right behind it and it's extremely hard not to dab. I took the pads off the fall zone and placed my thinnest dab in the dabbiest spot in order to make the lunge without dabbing.
content.protection: At least 2 pads and a few dab pads.
content.location: The problem to the left of Brainwash V4.Starts low on the two underclings and goes straight up.

content.description: The smaller blob right of Fox Buttress and left of the End Loop Boulder (closed).
